article.headline: Northern Iowa 85, UMKC 53
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Adam Viet scored 24 points and Eric Coleman had 15 points and 13 rebounds to help Northern Iowa rout Missouri-Kansas City 85-83 on Saturday night. Viet was 7-of-8 from 3-point range for the Panthers (8-1). "They played a 1-3-1 and it's tough for the baseline runner to get to me," Viet said. "Every time I'm in the game, I'm working hard. I play hard and try my best at all times. If we're winning then whatever is working is great." Grant Stout added 13 points and eight rebounds for Northern Iowa. Quinton Day led the Kangaroos (3-7) with 21 points.
